The next frontier for

EN

FR

Global development has been reshaped by multiple disruptive forces:
shrinking budgets, reduced reliance on foreign aid, and the rise of
transformative new technologies.


There is an immediate need and opportunity to transform how the world
fights poverty. At IDinsight, weve expanded our methods and
capabilities to meet todays urgency with the innovation and partnership
required to serve communities effectively.


Our work is pushing the sector to explore and invest in new ways of
delivering impact.

We stand at the close of a year that has tested the
foundations of our sector. While we have witnessed
remarkable resilience in the face of vanishing resources,
the weight of disrupted programs and the strain on
underserved populations is a burden we all share.


At IDinsight, we see a quiet revolution taking place.
Organizations are moving beyond defense and are
actively reimagining how to serve. We are collectively
figuring out how to deploy emerging tools and
opportunities in ways that meaningfully lift up
communities everywhere.

Rebecca Gong Sharp

CEO

Evolving our support to partners

As sector needs have evolved, weve broadened our services to support learning, innovation, and
scaling. We are demand-driven and guided by our partners needs and market signals. We have
continued to focus on impact, not methodology. Our partners tell us they value our ability to provide
practical, scalable evidence across an organizations entire lifecycle, from pilot to scale.


Over 15 years, weve expanded beyond impact evaluations to include rapid surveys, data and
engineering solutions, monitoring systems, AI-enabled approaches, and cost-effectiveness analysis.
Our refreshed strategy is focused on helping organizations overcome three barriers to social impact:
figuring out what works, learning and improving, and operating effectively at scale.

2025:

Diversifying our methods has opened up new avenues of impact. Were generating timely, decision-
relevant insights and strengthening the systems that improve lives at scale.


We measure our own effectiveness by the extent to which we contribute to improving lives and
strengthening our partners work.

lives improved

directed to

higher-impact work

Our impact metrics are a function of:

  • breadth (number of lives improved by our partners work),

  • depth (how significantly people are affected by our partners work),

  • contribution (the extent to which our work counterfactually
    improved the impact of the partners program).


We measure this against the cost of our service to determine our

cost-effectiveness. You can read more about our methodology here.
